There is nothing built in to help you. One option would be to set a &quot;cheating&quot; flag on the game object, and add a CHEAT command that sets it to true. Whenever you have a random chance, do something like:
if (RandomChance(40) or game.cheating)

It is none too slick, but will do the job. If you just use RandomChance, rather than GetRandomInt, you could re-write RandomChance itself to check game.cheating.
